I have tried a hundred things before I succeeded at any of them, and I’m still far from where I want to be in my music career. 

What I aim to remember everyday is how far I’ve come from where I started…how grateful I am to be able to have the ability to play music in the first place. We all have gifts that our God given. Yet, they are so easy to be taken for granted. My message is to help us remember how truly blessed we are, even in the midst of a crazy and broken world.

We will always fall, stumble, crash, and maybe even burn..

But it’s not what knocks us down that matters, it’s how we continue to pick ourselves back up.

What is something that you’re currently struggling with now? Leave a comment. I want to know, and I want to help encourage you!
